 "awd_abstract_narration": "9877022\r\nTeich\r\nThis project focuses on investigations of the use of entangled twin-photon beams as a nonclassical probe to obtain absorption and spectroscopic information from material media.  Measurements of the absorption cross section for twin photons will be carried out via photoemission experiments.  A phase-sensitive method that draws on the special relationship of the constituent entangled fields will allow the nonclassical component of the laser-matter interaction to be distinguished from the normal two-photon absorption.  The behavior of this nonclassical component will be examined as a function of the parameters of the entangled photon source.\r\n\r\n",
